00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:58.280
I want to calculate the distance
between adjacent planes of the same

00:17:58.280 --> 00:18:06.570
index. We can calculate the
distance between adjacent planes of

00:18:06.570 --> 00:18:14.850
the same index.
What is the distance between two

00:18:14.850 --> 00:18:22.090
adjacent planes of some value hkl?
That is given by the following

00:18:22.090 --> 00:18:28.290
formula, which again is a testimony
to Miller. The distance,

00:18:28.290 --> 00:18:34.490
and I am going to subscript it hkl
because they are all the same index,

00:18:34.490 --> 00:18:40.690
is given by a, which is the lattice
constant, divided by the square root

00:18:40.690 --> 00:18:46.890
of h squared plus k squared plus l
squared where a is the

00:18:46.890 --> 00:18:51.870
lattice constant.
Let's test it.

00:18:51.870 --> 00:18:55.620
If hkl is O, one,
O, trivially that separation should

00:18:55.620 --> 00:18:59.370
be a, the lattice constant.
And I think you can see that quite

00:18:59.370 --> 00:19:03.120
nicely up on the screen here.
It is one lattice constant between

00:19:03.120 --> 00:19:06.870
successive O, one,
O planes. Let's try it with O,

00:19:06.870 --> 00:19:10.620
two, O. It is going to be the
square root of two squared which is

00:19:10.620 --> 00:19:14.370
a over two. And,
sure enough, what is the distance

00:19:14.370 --> 00:19:18.120
between O, two,
O and the adjacent plane comparable

00:19:18.120 --> 00:19:22.720
to it?
It is only half a lattice constant.

00:19:22.720 --> 00:19:28.180
In essence, if you look here, every
O, two, O plane is only half a

00:19:28.180 --> 00:19:33.630
lattice constant away.
Every O, one, O plane is full

00:19:33.630 --> 00:19:39.080
lattice constant.
What you are really seeing then is

00:19:39.080 --> 00:19:44.540
that the d goes down,
the distance between planes goes

00:19:44.540 --> 00:20:03.413
down as the Miller index goes up.
What is the lowest Miller index?

00:19:30.000 --> 00:19:54.120
The lowest Miller index is O,
O, one. That is a lattice constant.

00:19:54.120 --> 00:19:58.240
That is the maximum separation.
And I think you can see that as you

00:19:58.240 --> 00:20:02.370
move hkl to higher values,
what you are doing is you are

00:20:02.370 --> 00:20:06.490
cutting at a higher angular slice.
And, as you cut for a higher

00:20:06.490 --> 00:20:10.620
angular slice,
the distance between successive

00:20:10.620 --> 00:20:14.740
planes is going to be reduced.
Mathematically what is going on,

00:20:14.740 --> 00:20:18.870
this is getting larger in the
denominator, this is remaining the

00:20:18.870 --> 00:20:38.540
same, so that distance becomes
closer and closer together.

