atomic structure by the use of
something that is comparable in

00:20:40.990 --> 00:20:44.590
dimension. If we are going to
measure the dimension of the human

00:20:44.590 --> 00:20:48.190
hair, we are not going to use a
yardstick. What kind of numbers are

00:20:48.190 --> 00:20:53.710
we looking at for these distances?
We are looking at something down

00:20:53.710 --> 00:21:01.140
around some number of angstroms.
We better find some tool that gives

00:21:01.140 --> 00:21:08.570
me units of some number of angstroms.
And that tool will be x-rays.

00:21:08.570 --> 00:21:25.406
Now let's look at characterization
of atomic structure by x-rays.

00:20:56.000 --> 00:21:25.120
Today I want to talk about the

00:21:25.120 --> 00:21:29.370
discovery of x-rays and the
underlying physics.

00:21:29.370 --> 00:21:33.620
And then next day we are going to
look at application.

00:21:33.620 --> 00:21:37.870
First of all, what are x-rays?
X-rays are a form of

00:21:37.870 --> 00:21:50.473
electromagnetic radiation.

00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:52.140
What does that mean?
That means all of these formulas

00:21:52.140 --> 00:21:57.280
apply. E equals h nu equals hc over
lambda equals hc nu bar.

00:21:57.280 --> 00:22:02.420
That applies. And the special
characteristic of x-rays is lambda

00:22:02.420 --> 00:22:07.560
is very short and typically there is
no hard rule on this,

00:22:07.560 --> 00:22:12.710
but just in round numbers we are
looking at between one one-hundredth

00:22:12.710 --> 00:22:17.850
to one hundred angstroms.
It is centered at about one

00:22:17.850 --> 00:22:37.166
angstrom where one angstrom is equal
to ten to the minus ten meters.

00:22:03.000 --> 00:22:26.630
I know it is not an SI unit,
and you know my aversion to the

00:22:26.630 --> 00:22:30.270
nanometer, but I will put it up here
because I am required by the

00:22:30.270 --> 00:22:33.900
International Union of Pure and
Applied Chemistry on the Systeme

00:22:33.900 --> 00:22:37.540
International to put this
contemptible unit here,

00:22:37.540 --> 00:22:41.180
but I love the angstroms.
This is just my personal preference.

00:22:41.180 --> 00:23:00.160
Let's plug in a value.
Suppose we have one angstrom as the

00:22:26.000 --> 00:22:32.000
wavelength if I use hc over lambda
where lambda equals one angstrom,

00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:38.000
or ten to the minus ten meters. I
end up with 12,

00:22:38.000 --> 00:22:44.000
00 electron volts per photon.
And this is clearly going to be

00:22:44.000 --> 00:22:50.000
powerful radiation.
Let's take a look here.

00:22:50.000 --> 00:22:56.000
I pulled this out of the back of
the text. This has ionization

00:22:56.000 --> 00:23:02.000
energies for the first
seven elements.

